%20India%20during%20Partition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20shares%20how%20the%20magnanimity%20of%20the%20event%20took%20years%20to%20settle%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20truck%20came%20to%20take%20the%20family%20to%20the%20station%20from%20where%20they%20would%20go%20to%20Amritsar%2C%20my%20great-grandfather%20quickly%20scribbled%20an%20%3Cem%3Eamanat%20nama%3C%2Fem%3E%20(trust%20document)%20bequeathing%20all%20their%20assets%20to%20their%20Muslim%20neighbours%20until%20the%20time%20they%20got%20back%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sahiba%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20be%20back%2C%E2%80%9D%20was%20the%20promise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFate%20knew%20better.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20while%20Amolak%E2%80%99s%20memories%20of%20Partition%20are%20coloured%20with%20fear%2C%20confusion%2C%20and%20grief%2C%20there%20are%20two%20stories%20he%20always%20tells%20Sahiba%2C%20to%20underscore%20how%2C%20even%20in%20the%20darkest%20of%20times%2C%20humanity%20breathed%20hope.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESahiba%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9COn%20the%20train%20journey%20to%20Amritsar%2C%20there%20was%20a%20rumour%20that%20the%20railway%20station%20water%20had%20been%20poisoned%20so%20that%20anyone%20who%20drank%20the%20water%20would%20die.%20A%20military%20personnel%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Muslim%2C%20who%20was%20assigned%20the%20duty%20of%20taking%20this%20cohort%20of%20people%20to%20the%20Indian%20side%20of%20the%20border%20%E2%80%94%20volunteered%20to%20drink%20the%20water%20and%20test%20it.%20%E2%80%98Even%20if%20it%20is%20poisoned%2C%20I%20will%20die.%20You%20will%20all%20be%20safe%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20told%20the%20people%20on%20the%20train.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20stories%20underscore%20an%20irony.%20While%20religion%20became%20the%20pretext%20of%20Partition%2C%20it%20also%20became%20the%20reason%20for%20hope.%20And%2C%20in%20these%20conversations%2C%20I%20found%20the%20answer%20to%20my%20question.%C2%A0%3C%2F