q%3Dbusinessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdd%20Business%20Insider%20as%20a%20preferred%20source%20on%20Google%20to%20see%20more%20of%20us.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2265a27422-42ae-4380-9b78-bc37738c8066%5C%22%3EStarting%20my%20career%20at%20Snap%20Inc.%20was%20a%20phenomenal%20experience%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20four%20years%20of%20study%20at%20Texas%20Tech%2C%20I%20completed%20two%20bachelor's%20degrees%2C%20in%20computer%20science%20and%20mathematics%2C%20with%20a%20minor%20in%20electrical%20engineering.%20I%20graduated%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20I%20landed%20my%20first%20full-time%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-job-market-hiring-skills%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoftware%20engineering%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Snap%20Inc.%2C%20starting%20in%20June%202021.%20My%20base%20salary%20was%20%24125%2C000%2C%20and%20I%20also%20got%20paid%20in%20bonuses%20and%20stock.%20I%20worked%20on%20Snapchat's%20messaging%20team%2C%20which%20was%20a%20core%20part%20of%20the%20business.%20Everyone%20I%20knew%20there%20was%20really%20smart%20and%20kind.%20There%20were%20great%20perks%20at%20that%20time%2C%20such%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsnap-ending-food-perk-citing-on-site-meals-and-rto-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeal%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20buy%20food%20every%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20I%20started%20a%20new%20job%20at%20ZipRecruiter%2C%20earning%20%24145%2C000%20in%20base%20salary%20plus%20a%20bonus%20and%20stock%20options.%20I%20wanted%20experience%20at%20a%20smaller%20team%20where%20I%20had%20more%20zero-to-one%20opportunities%20%E2%80%94%20a%20chance%20to%20build%20things%20completely%20from%20scratch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9fbf84d-a76e-4a4d-b5c7-ab8170f550ce%5C%22%3EI%20left%20traditional%20software%20engineering%20and%20started%20earning%20much%20more%20money%20in%20AI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%20first%20came%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November%202022%2C%20I%20knew%20the%20world%20was%20going%20to%20shift%20toward%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20goals%20have%20always%20been%20to%20maximize%20learning%20and%20build%20skills%20I%20can%20leverage%20later%20on.%20I%20felt%20getting%20more%20AI%20skills%20would%20be%20a%20good%20strategy%20for%20my%20future%2C%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-agents-adoption-top-tools-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eagentic%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20skills%20are%20more%20niche%20and%20emerging%20compared%20to%20mobile%20application%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20visa%20situation%20was%20the%20biggest%20obstacle%20to%20pivoting%20my%20career%20focus.%20I%20worked%20at%20Snapchat%20and%20ZipRecruiter%20on%20a%20type%20of%20student%20work%20authorization%20called%20Optional%20Practical%20Training%2C%20but%20it%20expired%20in%20July%202024%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20stop%20working%20at%20ZipRecruiter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20help%20from%20lawyers%2C%20I%20applied%20for%20a%20flexible%20type%20of%20visa%2C%20an%20agent-based%20O-1%20for%20%26quot%3Bextraordinary%26quot%3B%20talent.%20Rather%20than%20being%20tied%20to%20an%20employer%2C%20like%20I%20would%20be%20on%20the%20alternative%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fh-1b-visa-big-tech-immigration-green-card-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EH-1B%20employment%20visa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20lawyers%20arranged%20for%20a%20company%20to%20act%20as%20my%20%26quot%3Bagent%2C%26quot%3B%20sponsoring%20my%20application%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20I%20could%20work%20for%20multiple%20companies%20or%20become%20an%20entrepreneur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20received%20the%20O-1%20in%20September.%20Without%20the%20same%20visa%20concerns%20I%20had