s%2C%20which%20appeared%20to%20feature%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fupenn-student-olga-loiek-youtube-china-social-media-stole-face-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI-empowered%20deepfake%20face%20filters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side-by-side%20photos%20show%20the%20difference%20between%20Abe%20Lim's%20genuine%20photos%20and%20a%20screenshot%20of%20a%20video%20call%20that%20likely%20used%20an%20AI-empowered%20face%20filter.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688084473d5881a51c1dd2e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOn%20the%20left%20is%20a%20photo%20of%20Abe%20Lim%20used%20to%20scam%20an%20American%20man%20in%20California%20who%20spoke%20to%20me%2C%20and%20on%20the%20right%20is%20a%20screenshot%20of%20his%20video%20calls%20with%20a%20scam%20worker%20posing%20as%20Lim.%3Cp%3EAbe%20Lim%20and%20screenshot%20from%20victim%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20analyzing%20the%20screenshots%2C%20James%20said%20some%20images%20were%20highly%20suspicious%2C%20with%20tell-tale%20features%20of%20AI%20filters%20such%20as%20discoloration%20on%20the%20edges%20of%20the%20face%20and%20crispness%20around%20hair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20varying%20chin%20shapes%20and%20neck%20bumps%20in%20the%20webcam%20images%20also%20indicated%20the%20victims%20were%20likely%20called%20by%20at%20least%20two%20different%20women%20using%20deepfake%20filters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20it%20is%20very%20likely%20the%20images%20with%20white%20are%20deepfakes%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20screenshots%20show%20a%20woman%20speaking%20to%20a%20camera.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689adb94194a2d49b8ae623d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJames%20said%20it%20is%20highly%20likely%20a%20woman%20used%20a%20deepfake%20face%20filter%20of%20Lim%20in%20this%20video%20call%20with%20a%20victim.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20scam%20victim%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e7a8ef75-42ce-486c-8063-2c003ba9e668%5C%22%3EFraudsters%2C%20roaming%20free%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELim%20said%20what%20frustrates%20her%20most%20is%20that%20she's%20reported%20dozens%20of%20Instagram%20and%20Facebook%20accounts%20using%20her%20name%20and%20photos.%20Many%20were%20not%20taken%20down.%20A%20Facebook%20search%20of%20her%20name%20shows%20her%20photos%20on%20a%20dozen%20accounts%20purported%20to%20be%20of%20women%20living%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20and%20New%20York.%20Some%20claim%20to%20run%20a%20plastics%20recycling%20company%20with%20the%20same%20name%20as%20Lim's%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20verified%20account%20with%20this%20face%2C%26quot%3B%20Lim%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20herself.%20%26quot%3BYou%20shouldn't%20allow%20an%20account%20with%20the%20same%20photo%20to%20stay%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221594%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20screenshot%20shows%20several%20accounts%20of%20the%20same%20person%20with%20profile%20photos%20taken%20from%20Lim's%20social%20media.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6880859b3d5881a51c1dd2ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22656%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20search%20for%20Lim's%20name%20on%20Facebook%20in%20July%20yielded%20over%20a%20dozen%20results%20for%20accounts%20that%20use%20her%20name%20and%20profile%20picture.%3Cp%3EScreenshot%20via%20Facebook%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Meta%2C%20which%20runs%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20WhatsApp%2C%20told%20me%20via%20email%20that%20it%20was%20committed%20to%20keeping%20its%20platforms%20safe%20and%20that%20it%20continues%20to%20%26qu